<br>
This version of the game will address more Realm vs Realm combat and spell issues, as well as add some more spice to classes that desparately need it (such as the Blademaster and Mercenary). We'll also finish out the items on Mark's list - the one that he posted six weeks or so ago. See my previous note here on the Herald for a more itemized description of what we're working on. <br>
<br>
FYI, our user base is rising steadily by the day, helped by a big jump just after Christmas Day - no doubt many Camelot boxes were wrapped under Christmas trees until that day. On a recent evening, we just topped 37,000 simultaneous users. <br>
<br>
We'll keep you posted here on the Herald as the new version comes together - check back here for updates on the new features that are coming. </b><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Going over Mark's list (he wrote it about 7 days after release) the big updates that we can expect are <br>
<br>
1)Climbing <br>
2)Shapeshifting/Disguise <br>
3)New Weapon graphics (flaming swords and such) <br>
4)New npcs <br>
5)New (non-epic)Quests <br>
6)New NPC Models <br>
7)More Dungeon and Frontier Itemization <br>
8)Bounty point system and shops<br>
9)Hibernia Tweaks to fix weaknesses <br>
<br>
The next few were added on by Sanya in her before Christmas post <br>
<br>
10)Mez/Stun PVP Duration fixes <br>
11)Mez/Stun resists <br>
<br>
If they manage to follow through and get everything in, this will be a great (if not large) patch.  Expect to see this hit Pendragon in the next couple days, with a release patch late next week. <p><table><tr><td height=1 width=1><img src=http://divineguildpics.homestead.com/files/galadriel.gif border=0><td valign="bottom"><b><font size=4 color=0066FF>Salicia Swiftfoot</b><br></font><font size=2 color=red><i>Theurgist to the Stars</i></font><br><font size=2 color=0066FF><b>Galahad Server<br>DAoC Moderator for <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove>The Druids Grove</a></b></td>
